      "contentFieldValue": {
        "data": "<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n  <strong>Note:</strong> please note that Liferay has renamed its Liferay Experience\n  Could offerings to <i><strong>Liferay SaaS</strong></i> (formerly LXC) and\n  <i><strong>Liferay PaaS</strong></i> (formerly LXC-SM).\n</div>\n<aside class=\"alert alert-info\">\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>The following message was sent to those with active (as of Sept 15, 2022) Dynatrace subscriptions.</p>\n</aside>\n<p>As a part of your Liferay PaaS subscription, <a href=\"https://www.dynatrace.com/solutions/full-stack-monitoring/\">Dynatrace Full Stack Monitoring </a>was provided for advanced monitoring capabilities. </p>\n<p>An additional feature outside of the Dynatrace Full Stack Monitoring that some customers may have leveraged is the Dynatrace Digital Experience Monitoring (DEM) Capabilities. These capabilities are outside the scope of our offering and will be disabled as of <span class=\"wysiwyg-underline\"><strong>Oct 26, 2022</strong></span>.</p>\n<p>To clarify, core Dynatrace capabilities will still be available; however, all DEM functionality as well as monitoring that utilizes DEM units will no longer be available on the Dynatrace console, after it has  been disabled. See the <a href=\"https://www.dynatrace.com/support/help/monitoring-consumption/digital-experience-monitoring-units\">Dynatrace DEM Documentation </a>for a full list of functionality.</p>\n<p>If your solutions depend on features that accrue DEM units, you have the option to purchase a Dynatrace DEM subscription to replace the current Dynatrace Subscription included in your Liferay PaaS Dynatrace APM subscription. Please reach out to your Account Manager or Customer Success Manager who will connect you with a Dynatrace representative.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, please feel free to <a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/requests/new\" target=\"_self\">submit a ticket</a> and Liferay Support will be happy to assist you.</p>\n<p> </p>"
      },
